tip.text: Tried the pulled pork sandwich & spaghetti carbonara. Preferred the latter. Sandwich wasn't as great as I thought it would be. But the dishes are interesting enough for a return visit :)

Try their Peking duck, grilled Canadian cod fish, the four deluxe individual appetizer, homemade charcoal tofu with salted egg & 3 dim sum combination platter. The cumin & 5 spices duck was a let down
The Parisienne is my current fav! The brioche french toast stuffed with ham & cheese is to die for! And hollandaise on a fried egg is a nice twist to the usual eggs benedict! Slurps!

tip.text: The chef's special today, Tagliatelle with Beef Cheek was really good! Meat was so tender and pasta cooked just right.. If you like your pasta spicy, ask them to add some chili!
The chargrilled seafood spaghettini & wagyu beef pie is worth a try.. Don't bother with the rocky road cake though.
The beef noodle is almost as good as the original outlet in jalan silang. Don't mind paying slightly more for the convenience of a covered carpark & air conditioning while I enjoy my meal :)
Food is good bt service is slow. Mains took an hr to arrive bt the lady boss was kind enuff to offer us a free brownie which was yums! Try the onion soup, roastbeef pesto pasta & rigatoni aglio olio.
